<Base title="Hire me — Surya Kant Kashyap" description="What I'm open to, what I'm not, and how to start a conversation.">
  <article class="prose-post">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Hire me</h1>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-muted)] mb-10">
      I'm currently a senior engineer at <a href="https://www.kloudfuse.com/">Kloudfuse</a> and happy there, but I'm open to a small number of side engagements where the work is interesting and the scope is honest.
    </p>

    <h2>Where I add the most value</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Observability platform design.</strong> Metrics ingest, PromQL semantics, cardinality control, rollup pipelines, alerting. I've shipped end-to-end work in this space and have opinions about which choices age well.</li>
      <li><strong>Backend systems against columnar / OLAP stores.</strong> Apache Pinot specifically, but the patterns translate to ClickHouse, Druid, BigQuery, Snowflake. Query planning, push-down, schema design, replication trade-offs.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical writing for engineering teams.</strong> Internal docs, architecture write-ups, design reviews. I write better than the average senior engineer; this site is the evidence.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Engagement shapes I'm open to</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Short consulting (1–2 weeks): design review, architecture audit, "is this PromQL doing what we think it's doing" investigations.</li>
      <li>Longer technical-writing work: turning your team's internal expertise into shippable docs or external blog posts.</li>
      <li>Conference talks / podcasts about observability internals — happy to talk through whether the material I have fits your audience.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Not a fit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Full-time roles at the moment.</li>
      <li>Generic "implement this CRUD" work that has nothing to do with observability or data systems — there are better-fit engineers for that.</li>
      <li>Anything that requires me to relocate or work in conflict with my current employment.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Email is the most reliable: <a href="mailto:suryakant.kashyap@kloudfuse.com">suryakant.kashyap@kloudfuse.com</a>. A few lines about what you're trying to do and what's in the way is the right opener. I read everything; I reply when I can usefully help.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
